that allows me to know
what's gonna happen ahead of time.

1:41:09.480 --> 1:41:11.730
Then how come you didn't know
I was gonna pull a gun on you?

1:41:11.860 --> 1:41:14.360
I did. No, I didn't.

1:41:18.120 --> 1:41:20.280
-Is that okay?
-Yeah, it's good.

1:41:21.660 --> 1:41:22.950
One second.

1:41:27.830 --> 1:41:32.130
-I think that's gonna stay. Is that okay?
-Yeah, it's great.

1:41:32.250 --> 1:41:33.300
Okay.

1:41:35.220 --> 1:41:38.890
-All right. I'm not very good at this.
-You're very good.

1:41:52.530 --> 1:41:54.190
What's the matter?

1:41:55.240 --> 1:41:56.530
Jesus.

1:42:00.120 --> 1:42:02.120
I haven't changed a thing.

1:42:03.290 --> 1:42:05.540
I gotta go. And you gotta go with me.
Come on.

1:42:05.660 --> 1:42:06.870
What?

1:42:07.370 --> 1:42:09.830
-I thought you said I was safe now.
-I was wrong. I was wrong.

1:42:09.960 --> 1:42:12.170
You gotta go with me now. Right now.

1:42:12.920 --> 1:42:15.050
Wait, wait, wait! Don't answer it.

1:42:17.260 --> 1:42:18.680
Don't answer it. I'll prove it to you.

1:42:18.800 --> 1:42:19.840
That's your friend Beth calling.

1:42:19.970 --> 1:42:21.430
Let the machine pick it up.
She's gonna say,

1:42:21.550 --> 1:42:25.100
"Hi, Claire. It's Beth. Are you there?
I'm sorry to call you so early,

1:42:25.220 --> 1:42:28.230
"but when you didn't call me last night
I got worried."

1:42:28.770 --> 1:42:31.520
<i>Claire? Hi, it's Beth- Are you there?</i>

1:42:31.650 --> 1:42:33.020
<i>I'm sorry to call you so early,</i>

1:42:33.150 --> 1:42:35.150
<i>but you said you were gonna call me</i>
<i>when you got home,</i>

1:42:35.280 --> 1:42:37.030
<i>and when you didn't,</i>
<i>I started to get worried-</i>

1:42:37.150 --> 1:42:38.780
-Beth, is this a joke?
<i>-Oh, hey, hey! No-</i>

1:42:38.900 --> 1:42:40.700
<i>Like I said, I was just worried</i>
<i>about you, that's all-</i>

1:42:40.820 --> 1:42:42.830
I can't talk right now.
Someone's here. I'll call you later.

1:42:42.950 --> 1:42:43.990
<i>Claire---</i>

1:42:44.120 --> 1:42:47.200
Believe me, the only one
you're gonna be safe with is me.

1:42:47.330 --> 1:42:49.040
-Okay.
-Let's go.

1:42:54.170 --> 1:42:55.250
I don't understand.

1:42:55.380 --> 1:42:58.970
Why not just call the police
and have them arrest him at the dock?

1:42:59.550 --> 1:43:01.840
He'll set the bomb off
right there on the spot.

1:43:01.970 --> 1:43:03.470
He can't know he's been compromised

1:43:03.600 --> 1:43:05.600
until it's too late for him
to do anything about it.

1:43:05.720 --> 1:43:08.430
He'll set the timer, walk away on foot,
get on his motorcycle

1:43:08.560 --> 1:43:11.400
and ride to the Crescent City Bridge
to watch.

1:43:11.520 --> 1:43:15.150
Okay, then what?
You defuse the bomb?

1:43:15.650 --> 1:43:17.530
Then I defuse the bomb.

1:44:16.000 --> 1:44:17.840
There's my truck.

1:44:27.470 --> 1:44:29.350
-All these people.
-There he is.

1:44:29.470 --> 1:44:30.770
Where?

1:44:30.890 --> 1:44:33.940
You see the military jacket
coming this way?

1:44:37.980 --> 1:44:39.780
It's just what you said.

1:44:39.900 --> 1:44:43.110
All right,
you see those officers behind you?

1:44:43.240 --> 1:44:45.320
-Yeah.
-When the ferry pulls off,

1:44:45.450 --> 1:44:47.910
I want you to tell them about the bomb,
all right?

1:44:48.030 --> 1:44:50.370
-They'll believe me?
-They better believe you.

1:44:50.490 --> 1:44:52.710
-Come on, they'll arrest me.
-They won't arrest you.

1:44:52.830 --> 1:44:56.460
They'll take you into custody.
You'll be fine. That's a good thing.

1:44:56.880 --> 1:44:58.210
Don't turn around.

1:45:04.840 --> 1:45:06.050
Doug...

1:45:09.100 --> 1:45:10.470
Be careful.

1:45:43.460 --> 1:45:45.260
<i>Your attention, please-</i>

1:45:45.380 --> 1:45:47.930
<i>Passengers are not allowed</i>
<i>on the car deck</i>

1:45:48.050 --> 1:45:50.640
<i>when the ferry is in motion-</i>

1:45:57.310 --> 1:45:58.810
Sir! Sir.

1:45:58.940 --> 1:46:01.480
Excuse me, sir, you're gonna
have to move to the upper deck.

1:46:01.610 --> 1:46:04.190
-Passengers aren't allowed here.
-Okay.

1:46:43.650 --> 1:46:45.820
Can't believe it. They're right on time.

1:46:45.940 --> 1:46:48.240
Let's get these boys to their party.

1:47:10.930 --> 1:47:12.760
Mama!

1:48:55.360 --> 1:48:57.490
Excuse me, sir? Sir!

1:48:57.620 --> 1:49:00.950
There's no passengers allowed
on the car deck during transit.

1:49:04.290 --> 1:49:06.500
No passengers allowed, sir.

1:49:20.890 --> 1:49:22.020
Let's go! Let's go!

1:50:19.780 --> 1:50:21.490
It's destiny, Oerstadt.

1:50:22.370 --> 1:50:25.540
Satan reasons like a man,
but God thinks of eternity.

1:50:28.290 --> 1:50:29.750
What did you say?

1:50:29.880 --> 1:50:33.500
I'm saying it's gonna take
a little divine intervention here, buddy.

1:50:35.510 --> 1:50:37.090
I'm coming out.

1:50:45.270 --> 1:50:46.850
What'd you say?

1:50:47.980 --> 1:50:49.900
I thought you were a patriot.

1:50:50.020 --> 1:50:51.230
Oh, I am.

1:50:52.440 --> 1:50:54.610
Patriotism requires sacrifice.

1:50:55.230 --> 1:50:58.490
-I'm willing to sacrifice.
-Yeah? Who? Her? Me?

1:50:58.610 --> 1:51:01.160
You're willing to sacrifice others,
but not yourself.

1:51:01.280 --> 1:51:05.620
The Tree of Liberty must be refreshed
with the blood of patriots and tyrants.

1:51:06.830 --> 1:51:07.910
Right.

1:51:08.040 --> 1:51:11.750
Sometimes a little human collateral
is the cost of freedom, isn't it?

1:51:16.800 --> 1:51:18.760
Who are you, Oerstadt?

1:51:21.720 --> 1:51:23.100
Who are you?

1:51:25.890 --> 1:51:27.930
It's not supposed to be this way.

1:51:55.840 --> 1:51:57.460
You all right?

1:52:00.630 --> 1:52:03.550
-I killed him.
-No, you didn't. I did.

1:52:03.680 --> 1:52:06.510
<i>It's 10:48 on Fat Tuesday, Mardi Gras-</i>

1:52:06.640 --> 1:52:09.230
<i>Now let's go back in time to 1964-</i>

1:52:09.350 --> 1:52:11.390
-We're gonna die.
-No, we're not.

1:52:11.520 --> 1:52:13.980
<i>---on 105-3 FM,</i>
<i>the heart of New Orleans-</i>

1:52:14.100 --> 1:52:15.940
Hit the gas.

1:52:16.110 --> 1:52:17.570
Hit the gas!

1:52:23.280 --> 1:52:26.870
Put your hands in the air
and step out of the vehicle now!

1:52:28.580 --> 1:52:30.960
We get out now, everybody dies.

1:52:32.460 --> 1:52:34.670
You have until the count of three!

1:52:34.790 --> 1:52:35.790
Hit it.

1:52:35.920 --> 1:52:36.960
One...

1:54:49.590 --> 1:54:53.060
But my daughter's on that ferry.
Please. Please.

1:54:54.270 --> 1:54:56.430
Oh, God, my daughter!

1:55:10.950 --> 1:55:12.410
Chrissie!

1:55:13.120 --> 1:55:14.240
Chrissie!

1:55:14.370 --> 1:55:16.750
-Oh, Chrissie! Chrissie!
-It's my mom!

1:55:16.870 --> 1:55:17.960
Mom!

1:55:24.040 --> 1:55:27.260
Ma'am? We're gonna need you
to stay right here.

1:55:27.380 --> 1:55:29.470
Someone's on the way over
to take a statement

1:55:29.590 --> 1:55:31.930
and ask you some questions, okay?

1:55:56.870 --> 1:55:59.120
-Bobby.
-Doug.

1:55:59.250 --> 1:56:00.620
-How you doing?
-All right.

1:56:00.750 --> 1:56:03.210
Got a live one over here.
Pulled her out of the drink.

1:56:03.330 --> 1:56:05.670
Somehow involved in all of this.

1:56:09.510 --> 1:56:10.590
Okay.

1:56:16.390 --> 1:56:19.180
-How you doing?
-Doug?

1:56:20.270 --> 1:56:21.690
That's right.

1:56:25.060 --> 1:56:27.020
-You okay?
-Yeah.

1:56:31.860 --> 1:56:33.200
Have we met?

1:56:35.120 --> 1:56:37.870
Yeah. Yeah, we have.

1:56:41.750 --> 1:56:43.370
It's okay. Come on.

1:56:44.330 --> 1:56:45.540
Come on.

1:57:00.640 --> 1:57:02.430
-You okay?
-Yeah.

1:57:02.560 --> 1:57:04.230
-You sure?
-Yeah.

1:57:04.520 --> 1:57:07.230
Okay. I'll get you warmed up.

1:57:17.120 --> 1:57:18.450
What is it?

1:57:20.240 --> 1:57:21.580
What is it?

1:57:26.790 --> 1:57:27.880
Doug.

1:57:30.000 --> 1:57:33.670
What if you had to tell someone
the most important thing in the world,

1:57:33.800 --> 1:57:36.510
but you knew they'd never believe you?

1:57:37.850 --> 1:57:39.050
I'd try.
